0051|+TEXTS? þ PRINT CUR+1,E TO q1k_03.html
0052|- include HTML40.DEV
0053|- include Q.DV2
0054|- [HelpText]
0055|#TEXTS=<list_of_text_specifications>
S   |       <                           >
0056|*gives a list of extra texts to be written in the current graph. Each
0057|*member of this list is a word (name of the text), and any such a text
0058|*is given in the form
0060|*   <name_of_the_text>=<string>,x,y
S   |    <                > <      >
0062|*where (x,y) is the starting point of the text in plotting units and
0063|*<string> is a string without spaces and ','s to be written. Possible
S   | <      >
0064|*spaces should be replaced by '_'s. Similarly ','s must be replaced by
0065|S';'s.  (';' and '_' are given as '\;' and '\_'.)
S   |        88888888888888888888888888888888888888888
0066|*Example: TEXTS=T1,T2 T1=[Times(15)],SURVO_84C,500,50 T2=9_May_1987,650,50
0067|*As in T1, a control code in brackets may precede the text.
0069|*If a text is to be plotted in parentheses or brackets, a control
0070|*code (in brackets or parentheses) must precede it:
0071|*Example: TEXTS=L1,Label2  L1=[Times(15)],(SURVO_84C),100,300
0072|*                          Label2=(),[4_Jan_1992],400,50
0073|*In Label2, () is a dummy control code. The texts to be plotted will
0074|*be    (SURVO 84C)   and   [4 Jan 1992]  .
0076|*New alternative: Text on multiple lines (see next page!)
0079|*Text on multiple lines:
0081|*Any of the text names, say TL, listed in the TEXTS specification,
0082|*can also refer to a set of several lines. In this case TL has the
0083|*form
0084|*   TL=#LINES:<first_line>,<last_line>,x,y,<line_spacing>
S   |              <          > <         >     <            >
0085|*where (x,y) is the starting point of the first line. The following
0086|*lines will be plotted below the first one by using the given
0087|*line spacing.
0088|*Example:
0089|*................................................................................
0090|*GPLOT Y(X)=A*sin(X)  / A=0,10,1 X=[line_width(5)][RED],-pi,pi,pi/20
0091|*MODE=EGA               pi=3.141592653589793 XSCALE=-pi,0,pi
0092|*TEXTS=T T=[Times(20)],#LINES:CUR+3,CUR+5,50,270,30
0093|*This is a family
0094|*of sinus curves
0095|*with different amplitudes.
0096|*FRAMES=F F=40,200,280,100,4    FRAME=0
0097|*................................................................................
