0162|- include HTML40.DEV
0163|- include Q.DV2
0164|- [HelpText]
0165|*A (filled) polygon can be plotted by a PLOT operation of the form
0166|*PLOT <data>,<xvar>,<yvar> / LINE=POLYGON,<fill_index>
S   |      <    > <    > <    >                <          >
0167|*The coordinates of the vertices are given by the <xvar> and <yvar>
S   |                                                  <    >     <    >
0168|*variables and the polygon is filled by the shading (or color)
0169|*given by the (optional) <fill_index>.
S   |                         <          >
0170|*........................................................................
0171|*Example:
0172|*DATA POLY6:(X,Y) 0,0 4,1 3,3 2,2 0,2 1,1 END
0174|*GPLOT POLY6,X,Y / LINE=POLYGON,5 GRID=1,1
0175|*........................................................................
0176|*A more general form on the next page!
0178|*If <yvar> has missing values, a sequence of polygons is plotted.
S   |    <    >
0179|*A missing <yvar> value terminates plotting of the current polygon
S   |           <    >
0180|*and starts a new one with <fill_index> given by the <xvar> value.
S   |                           <          >              <    >
0181|*If <fill_index> is 0, only the edges of the polygon are drawn.
S   |    <          >
0182|*LINE=[line_width(0)],POLYGON,<fill_index>
S   |                              <          >
0183|*means that the edges are not drawn but the polygon is filled.
0184|*........................................................................
0185|*Example: Three partially overlapping polygons
0186|*DATA POLY14:(X,Y) 2,0.5 4,3 0,0 3,- 0,2.5 0,1 4,2 3,2.7 2,-
0187|*                  4,0 4,1 2.8,1.2 2.5,3 2.3,0
0189|*GPLOT POLY14,X,Y / LINE=POLYGON,5 GRID=1,1
0190|*ROP=9 (Test various raster options using ROP values 0,1,2,...,15!)
0191|*........................................................................
0193|- shadow a: [LINK(q1k_06.html)]
